An element with a role that hides child elements contains focusable child elements.
role=option
This role element marks child elements as presentational, which hides them from the accessibility tree, but some of these children are focusable, so they can be navigated to, but are not voiced in a screen reader.

An element with a role that hides child elements contains focusable child elements.
role=option
This role element marks child elements as presentational, which hides them from the accessibility tree, but some of these children are focusable, so they can be navigated to, but are not voiced in a screen reader.
Line 3657 WCAG 2.1 A 1.3.1 Section 508 (2017) A 1.3.1 ARIA 1.1 Presentational Children
An element with role=option must be contained in, or owned by, an element with role=listbox
Line 3657 WCAG 2.1 A 4.1.1 Section 508 (2017) A 4.1.1

  • Add an aria-label attribute
  • Add an aria-labelledby attribute
  • Add an img alt attribute if the button contains an img element
